What is Nexba?

NEXBA is one of the fastest growing Naturally Sugar Free brands. The business was founded with NEXBA in traditional beverage categories such as soft drink and iced tea. However, it has experienced significant success in Kombucha and other emerging beverage categories including its new natural Energy Drinks launched in the UK and the upcoming Spritz range about to be launched in Australia.

NEXBA’s first product beyond beverages, “Liquid Brekkie,” has outperformed sales expectations to date, with strong brand recognition and clear cross-product consumer purchasing plans to further expand its “beyond beverage offering.” NEXBA’s proprietary Naturally Sugar Free GoodSweet® Sweetener now with patent secured in Australia, enables further platform expansion.

The Business has continued to deliver impressive financial performance and global expansion. Relevantly, FY23 (June) net sales are forecast to be A$32.4 m net sales with $5.5 m gross profit in FY23 (despite impacts from COVID and Floods in Australia). NEXBA is now firmly established in Australia and the UK with recent (active) distribution agreements unlocking other European and Asian market expansion and their Kombucha product already on-shelf in Carrefour, France’s #1 grocery chain.

The Business is, therefore, pursuing a further capital raise from a targeted group of existing shareholders and new investors. This capital raise is poised to accelerate the company’s performance and fast-track high-growth profitability within the next three years.

With enhanced manufacturing and distribution capabilities already underway in EMEA and APAC, and the establishment of the Goodsweet® Group to support multi-market and multi-category growth, this capital raise extension offers the business the opportunity to pursue a bolder business plan, to focus on delivering profitability in each division sooner and, ultimately, create a stronger Group platform that will unlock greater value and liquidity options for all shareholders over time.

Problem and Market

Global better-for-you mega trends


Food as Medicine
Consumers are becoming more aware of the health risks associated with sugary and processed foods and shifting to better-for-you alternatives

Functional Benefits
To avoid foods associated with dietary risks, consumers are increasingly seeking nutrient‐dense, natural foods that provide functional benefits for their health

Natural & Clean Label
Consumers are increasingly favouring foods and beverages made with all-natural ingredients free from artificials

The Nexba Solution

Authenticity multinationals can’t replicate


Consumers are turning away from multinationals offering sub-standard faux-health alternatives while NEXBA has clear and consistent product promises for consumers. Australia is a country with world-class quality and a wholesome approach with an excellent and enforced quality control regime.

NEXBA re-enforces the “Australian innovation” quality tag with the “underdog” image of a young, dynamic and high growth company. Identifying with consumers, the “Aussie Boys” authenticity of the founders reflects this ‘no worries mate’ and ‘Naturally Brave’ mantra perfectly.

Growth Strategy

NEXBA is building the first Multi-Category & Multi-Market Food and Beverage platform, underpinned by their proprietary ‘Goodsweet®’ Sweetener blend, accelerating the Food and Beverage industry by doing good and removing sugar and artificials from the Worlds Diet…

  • New Australia partnership planned in 2023 to expand distribution to higher margin route, food service and cafe markets channel, target to build incremental $10 million net sales channel over 3 years.
  • Evolution to Goodsweet Group to catapult the company’s ambitious growth strategy - build and acquire better-for-you brands, ingredient licensing, and consumer-direct brand.
  • GOODSWEET Group Base Business Plan is set to achieve >A$100m in value over the next 3 years with significant scope for further performance via imminent Brand M&A opportunities (Q1, 2023).
  • New EMEA partnerships with Tarka Springs (UK) and Krynica Vitamin (Poland) enabling local manufacturing, multiplying of distribution points and driving profitability in EBITDA.
  • New ANZ partnership with Nippy’s in Q1, 2023 to expand distribution to highly lucrative route, food service and cafe markets, building a $30 million sales channel over 3 to 5 years.
  • NEXBA has strong traction beyond Australia supporting the global expansion case across Europe.
  • The UK market functions as a beachhead for regional expansion into Europe – 210% growth in the UK, despite severe lockdown measures remaining throughout 2021.
  • Extensive NEW product development roadmap coming to market over 18 to 24 months supported by targeted new channel expansion.
  • #1 prompted brand awareness in Kombucha – brand awareness grew across product categories, demonstrating the halo effect of stronger marketing programs and activating in-store.
  • 3rd biggest contributor to total ambient aisle beverage sales in Coles (behind CCA and Schweppes).
  • #1 Retail Kombucha brand in the UK, growing share each month and outselling nearest rival by over 50%.
  • Early success into South Korea further proving the breadth of opportunity UK market functions as a beachhead for regional expansion into Europe – 210% growth in UK, despite severe.
  • Targeting Group EBITDA >$6m by FY26E and positive EBITDA expected in Australia for FY23F with significant revenue growth and margin improvement supporting sustained profitability across APAC and EMEA.
  • Liquid Brekkie represented NEXBA’s first product launch beyond beverages and has outperformed sales expectations to date, with strong brand recognition and clear cross-product consumer synergy across platform – already +5% market share in Woolworths.
  • Despite lockdowns in ANZ and UK / European markets, and ongoing customer and consumer uncertainty NEXBA has delivered strong growth in both markets over the last 12 months.

Exit Strategy

This ‘Series B’ capital raise extension offers the business the opportunity to execute a bolder business plan, to focus on delivering profitability in each division and ultimately create a stronger Goodsweet® Group platform that will unlock greater value and liquidity options for all shareholders over time.

The Founders are seeking investors who share their vision to create positive change with brands that taste good and do good.

The Founders' ambition is to continue to drive the business into the next phase, further driving internal governance and management expertise to enhance accountability and performance in both mitigation of risks and unlocking of opportunities.

They are now pursuing a short-term capital raise from a targeted group of existing shareholders and select aligned new investors who would represent minority investors in the group.

We will return to the capital market at a superior valuation once we deliver on the initiatives outlined in the use of proceeds. We anticipate this to be a two to three-year horizon and it is at this point we expect the opportunity for a significant liquidity event for investors.
